Package ie.gmit.ngrams

Classes for generate the kmrs and identify a language

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Countator<T,K extends Entry<T>>
    Used for counts objects of type T , the count is store in K.
    DatabaseInterface
    Define interface methods for access database
    DistanceCalculator<T>
    Define a distance between two objects of the same type.
    Entry<T>
    A entry of a T elements that keep count and rank of it.
    KmerGenerator<T>
    Generate kmers from a line of characters.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractKmerGenerator<T>
    ConcurrentLanguageEntryCountator<T>
    Defene a Countator for language entry
    CreateMapOneTask
    Create one map for a language, generates the kmers from a string input.
    Database
    A databse base with one entry for each language, contains methods for compare other entry's against the stored entries.
    DataCreationTask
    Create database (subject for queries) using multiple threads.
    FileParser
    Parse a file, put each line of the file into a output queue as CharSequence, a poison will indicate the end of the file.
    LanguageEntry<T>
    Entry implementation for a specific language.
    LanguageEntryAbstractCountator<T>
    Defene a Countator for language entry
    LongKmer3Generator
    Generate kmers of size 3
    LongKmer4Generator
    Mapper<T>
    Generates kmers from input queue of CharSequence then they are counted in a map queue.
    OutOfPlaceMetric
    Store a out of place metric distance for a language
    OutOfPlaceMetricDistance
    Calcualte out of place metric distance of 2 languages
    Reducer<T extends java.lang.Number>  
    StringPoison
    Poison for CharSequence queue, this is the queue for reading the file.
  • Enum Summary

    KmersSize
    Define the type of kmers
    Language  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NoMoreKmersException
    RuntimeException throwed when there are no more kmers.
